## Why we cannnot use Conda
For individual use conda is free but for commerical use (large organisations) you need to purchase licensing. So instead we need to use a subbranch of conda with is miniconda/miniforge.

## Using conda-forge/miniforge
Miniforge is very similar to conda but just have a seperate command prompt and some different keywords.\
[Here is the git page for conda-forge](https://github.com/conda-forge/miniforge)


## Creating environments
Theres a good guide [here](https://docs.conda.io/projects/conda/en/latest/user-guide/tasks/manage-environments.html) on setting up enviornments.
